\
## \uc0\u55357 \u56589  Lab Objectives\
- Deploy a Windows VM in Azure\
- Generate successful login events\
- Identify Event ID 4624 (Successful Logon)\
- Analyze log fields such as:\
  - Logon Type\
  - Account Name\
  - Process Name\
  - Timestamp\
- Document findings as evidence of threat detection\
\
---\
\
## \uc0\u55357 \u56522  Key Findings\
During this lab:\
- Multiple **successful logon events (Event ID 4624)** were identified\
- Logon Type **5 (Service Logon)** was observed\
- SYSTEM-level processes such as `services.exe` generated authentication events\
- Logs confirmed successful authentication activity on the VM\
\
These events demonstrate how SIEM tools detect authentication behavior and help security teams monitor system access.\
